1.name: bulbasaur
1.description: It can go for days without eating a single morsel. In the bulb on its back, it stores energy.

2.name: ivysaur
2.description: The bud on its back grows by drawing energy. It gives off an aroma when it is ready to bloom.

3.name: venusaur
3.description: The flower on its back catches the sun’s rays. The sunlight is then absorbed and used for energy.

4.name: charmander
4.description: The flame at the tip of its tail makes a sound as it burns. You can only hear it in quiet places.

5.name: charmeleon
5.description: Tough fights could excite this Pokémon. When excited, it may breathe out bluish-white flames.

6.name: charizard
6.description: When this Pokémon expels a blast of superhot fire, the red flame at the tip of its tail burns more intensely.

7.name: squirtle
7.description: Shoots water at prey while in the water. Withdraws into its shell when in danger.

8.name: wartortle
8.description: When tapped on its head, this Pokémon will pull it in, but its tail will still stick out a little bit.

9.name: blastoise
9.description: Once it takes aim at its enemy, it blasts out water with even more force than a fire hose.

10.name: caterpie
10.description: If you touch the feeler on top of its head, it will release a horrible stink to protect itself.

11.name: metapod
11.description: Hardens its shell to protect itself. However, a large impact may cause it to pop out of its shell.

12.name: butterfree
12.description: Its wings, covered with poisonous powder, repel water. This allows it to fly in the rain.

13.name: weedle
13.description: Beware of the sharp stinger on its head. It hides in grass and bushes where it eats leaves.

14.name: kakuna
14.description: Able to move only slightly. When endangered, it may stick out its stinger and poison its enemy.

15.name: beedrill
15.description: It has three poisonous stingers on its forelegs and its tail. They are used to jab its enemy repeatedly.

16.name: pidgey
16.description: Very docile. If attacked, it will often kick up sand to protect itself rather than fight back.

17.name: pidgeotto
17.description: This Pokémon is full of vitality. It constantly flies around its large territory in search of prey.

18.name: pidgeot
18.description: This Pokémon flies at Mach 2 speed, seeking prey. Its large talons are feared as wicked weapons.

19.name: rattata
19.description: Will chew on anything with its fangs. If you see one, you can be certain that 40 more live in the area.

20.name: raticate
20.description: Its hind feet are webbed. They act as flippers, so it can swim in rivers and hunt for prey.

21.name: spearow
21.description: Inept at flying high. However, it can fly around very fast to protect its territory.

22.name: fearow
22.description: A Pokémon that dates back many years. If it senses danger, it flies high and away, instantly.

23.name: ekans
23.description: The older it gets, the longer it grows. At night, it wraps its long body around tree branches to rest.

24.name: arbok
24.description: The frightening patterns on its belly have been studied. Six variations have been confirmed.

25.name: pikachu
25.description: This forest-dwelling Pokémon stores electricity in its cheeks, so you’ll feel a tingly shock if you touch it.

26.name: raichu
26.description: When electricity builds up inside its body, it becomes feisty. It also glows in the dark.

27.name: sandshrew
27.description: Its body is dry. When it gets cold at night, its hide is said to become coated with a fine dew.

28.name: sandslash
28.description: It is skilled at slashing enemies with its claws. If broken, they start to grow back in a day.

29.name: nidoran-f
29.description: A mild-mannered Pokémon that does not like to fight. Beware—its small horn secretes venom.

30.name: nidorina
30.description: When resting deep in its burrow, its barbs always retract. This is proof that it is relaxed.

31.name: nidoqueen
31.description: Tough scales cover the sturdy body of this Pokémon. It appears that the scales grow in cycles.

32.name: nidoran-m
32.description: Its large ears are always kept upright. If it senses danger, it will attack with a poisonous sting.

33.name: nidorino
33.description: Its horn contains venom. If it stabs an enemy with the horn, the impact makes the poison leak out.

34.name: nidoking
34.description: Its steel-like hide adds to its powerful tackle. Its horns are so hard, they can pierce a diamond.

35.name: clefairy
35.description: Adored for their cute looks and playfulness. They are thought to be rare, as they do not appear often.

36.name: clefable
36.description: They appear to be very protective of their own world. It is a kind of fairy, rarely seen by people.

37.name: vulpix
37.description: Both its fur and its tails are beautiful. As it grows, the tails split and form more tails.

38.name: ninetales
38.description: According to an enduring legend, nine noble saints were united and reincarnated as this Pokémon.

39.name: jigglypuff
39.description: Uses its cute round eyes to enrapture its foe. It then sings a pleasing melody that lulls the foe to sleep.

40.name: wigglytuff
40.description: Its body is very elastic. By inhaling deeply, it can continue to inflate itself without limit.

41.name: zubat
41.description: Emits ultrasonic cries while it flies. They act as a sonar used to check for objects in its way.

42.name: golbat
42.description: It attacks in a stealthy manner, without warning. Its sharp fangs are used to bite and to suck blood.

43.name: oddish
43.description: It may be mistaken for a clump of weeds. If you try to yank it out of the ground, it shrieks horribly.

44.name: gloom
44.description: Smells incredibly foul! However, around one out of a thousand people enjoy sniffing its nose-bending stink.

45.name: vileplume
45.description: Flaps its broad flower petals to scatter its poisonous pollen. The flapping sound is very loud.

46.name: paras
46.description: Burrows under the ground to gnaw on tree roots. The mushrooms on its back absorb most of the nutrition.

47.name: parasect
47.description: The bug host is drained of energy by the mushroom on its back. The mushroom appears to do all the thinking.

48.name: venonat
48.description: Its large eyes act as radar. In a bright place, you can see that they are clusters of many tiny eyes.

49.name: venomoth
49.description: The powdery scales on its wings are hard to remove from skin. They also contain poison that leaks out on contact.

50.name: diglett
50.description: It prefers dark places. It spends most of its time underground, though it may pop up in caves.

51.name: dugtrio
51.description: A team of triplets that can burrow to a depth of 60 miles. It’s reported that this triggers an earthquake.

52.name: meowth
52.description: Appears to be more active at night. It loves round and shiny things. It can’t stop itself from picking them up.

53.name: persian
53.description: The gem in its forehead glows on its own! It walks with all the grace and elegance of a proud queen.

54.name: psyduck
54.description: Always tormented by headaches. It uses psychic powers, but whether it intends to do so is not known.

55.name: golduck
55.description: Its long, slim limbs end in broad flippers. They are used for swimming gracefully in lakes.

56.name: mankey
56.description: An agile Pokémon that lives in trees. It angers easily and will not hesitate to attack anything.

57.name: primeape
57.description: It stops being angry only when nobody else is around. To view this moment is very difficult.

58.name: growlithe
58.description: A Pokémon with a friendly nature. However, it will bark fiercely at anything invading its territory.

59.name: arcanine
59.description: A legendary Pokémon in the East. Many people are charmed by the grace and beauty of its running.

60.name: poliwag
60.description: The direction of the spiral on the belly differs by area. It is more adept at swimming than walking.

61.name: poliwhirl
61.description: Under attack, it uses its belly spiral to put the foe to sleep. It then makes its escape.

62.name: poliwrath
62.description: Swims powerfully using all the muscles in its body. It can even overtake world-class swimmers.

63.name: abra
63.description: Sleeps 18 hours a day. If it senses danger, it will teleport itself to safety even as it sleeps.

64.name: kadabra
64.description: Many odd things happen if this Pokémon is close by. For example, it makes clocks run backward.

65.name: alakazam
65.description: A Pokémon that can memorize anything. It never forgets what it learns—that’s why this Pokémon is smart.

66.name: machop
66.description: Very powerful in spite of its small size. Its mastery of many types of martial arts makes it very tough.

67.name: machoke
67.description: The belt around its waist holds back its energy. Without it, this Pokémon would be unstoppable.

68.name: machamp
68.description: One arm alone can move mountains. Using all four arms, this Pokémon fires off awesome punches.

69.name: bellsprout
69.description: Prefers hot and humid places. It ensnares tiny bugs with its vines and devours them.

70.name: weepinbell
70.description: When hungry, it swallows anything that moves. Its hapless prey is dissolved by strong acids.

71.name: victreebel
71.description: Lures prey with the sweet aroma of honey. Swallowed whole, the prey is dissolved in a day, bones and all.

72.name: tentacool
72.description: It can sometimes be found all dry and shriveled up on a beach. Toss it back into the sea to revive it.

73.name: tentacruel
73.description: Its 80 tentacles can stretch and contract freely. They wrap around prey and weaken it with poison.

74.name: geodude
74.description: Commonly found near mountain trails and the like. If you step on one by accident, it gets angry.

75.name: graveler
75.description: Often seen rolling down mountain trails. Obstacles are just things to roll straight over, not avoid.

76.name: golem
76.description: Once it sheds its skin, its body turns tender and whitish. Its hide hardens when it’s exposed to air.

77.name: ponyta
77.description: Capable of jumping incredibly high. Its hooves and sturdy legs absorb the impact of a hard landing.

78.name: rapidash
78.description: Just loves to run. If it sees something faster than itself, it will give chase at top speed.

79.name: slowpoke
79.description: Incredibly slow and sluggish. It is quite content to loll about without worrying about the time.

80.name: slowbro
80.description: Lives lazily by the sea. If the Shellder on its tail comes off, it becomes a Slowpoke again.

81.name: magnemite
81.description: It is hatched with the ability to defy gravity. It floats while emitting powerful electromagnetic waves.

82.name: magneton
82.description: Generates strange radio signals. It raises the temperature by 3.6 degrees Fahrenheit within 3,300 feet.

83.name: farfetchd
83.description: They live where reedy plants grow. Farfetch’d are rarely seen, so it’s thought their numbers are decreasing.

84.name: doduo
84.description: Its short wings make flying difficult. Instead, this Pokémon runs at high speed on developed legs.

85.name: dodrio
85.description: One of Doduo’s two heads splits to form a unique species. It runs close to 40 mph in prairies.

86.name: seel
86.description: Loves freezing-cold conditions. Relishes swimming in a frigid climate of around 14 degrees Fahrenheit.

87.name: dewgong
87.description: Its entire body is a snowy white. Unharmed by even intense cold, it swims powerfully in icy waters.

88.name: grimer
88.description: Made of congealed sludge. It smells too putrid to touch. Even weeds won’t grow in its path.

89.name: muk
89.description: Smells so awful, it can cause fainting. Through degeneration of its nose, it lost its sense of smell.

90.name: shellder
90.description: The shell can withstand any attack. However, when it is open, the tender body is exposed.

91.name: cloyster
91.description: For protection, it uses its harder-than-diamond shell. It also shoots spikes from the shell.

92.name: gastly
92.description: Said to appear in decrepit, deserted buildings. It has no real shape, as it appears to be made of a gas.

93.name: haunter
93.description: By licking, it saps the victim’s life. It causes shaking that won’t stop until the victim’s demise.

94.name: gengar
94.description: A Gengar is close by if you feel a sudden chill. It may be trying to lay a curse on you.

95.name: onix
95.description: Burrows at high speed in search of food. The tunnels it leaves are used as homes by Diglett.

96.name: drowzee
96.description: If you sleep by it all the time, it will sometimes show you dreams it had eaten in the past.

97.name: hypno
97.description: Avoid eye contact if you come across one. It will try to put you to sleep by using its pendulum.

98.name: krabby
98.description: Its pincers are superb weapons. They sometimes break off during battle, but they grow back fast.

99.name: kingler
99.description: One claw grew massively and is as hard as steel. It has 10,000-horsepower strength. However, it is too heavy.

100.name: voltorb
100.description: It is said to camouflage itself as a Poké Ball. It will self-destruct with very little stimulus.

101.name: electrode
101.description: Stores electrical energy inside its body. Even the slightest shock could trigger a huge explosion.

102.name: exeggcute
102.description: The heads attract each other and spin around. There must be six heads for it to maintain balance.

103.name: exeggutor
103.description: Its cries are very noisy. This is because each of the three heads thinks about whatever it likes.

104.name: cubone
104.description: Wears the skull of its deceased mother. Its cries echo inside the skull and come out as a sad melody.

105.name: marowak
105.description: Small and weak, this Pokémon is adept with its bone club. It has grown more vicious over the ages.

106.name: hitmonlee
106.description: When kicking, the sole of its foot turns as hard as a diamond on impact and destroys its enemy.

107.name: hitmonchan
107.description: Punches in corkscrew fashion. It can punch its way through a concrete wall like a drill.

108.name: lickitung
108.description: Its tongue spans almost seven feet and moves more freely than its forelegs. Its licks can cause paralysis.

109.name: koffing
109.description: In hot places, its internal gases could expand and explode without any warning. Be very careful!

110.name: weezing
110.description: This Pokémon lives and grows by absorbing poison gas, dust, and germs that exist inside garbage.

111.name: rhyhorn
111.description: A Pokémon with a one-track mind. Once it charges, it won’t stop running until it falls asleep.

112.name: rhydon
112.description: Its brain developed when it began walking on its hind legs. Its armor-like hide even repels molten lava.

113.name: chansey
113.description: A gentle and kindhearted Pokémon that shares its nutritious eggs if it sees an injured Pokémon.

114.name: tangela
114.description: Its identity is obscured by masses of thick blue vines. The vines are said to never stop growing.

115.name: kangaskhan
115.description: Raises its young in its belly pouch. Won’t run from any fight to keep its young protected.

116.name: horsea
116.description: If it senses any danger, it will vigorously spray water or a special type of ink from its mouth.

117.name: seadra
117.description: Touching the back fin causes numbness. It hooks its tail to coral to stay in place while sleeping.

118.name: goldeen
118.description: When it is time for them to lay eggs, they can be seen swimming up rivers and falls in large groups.

119.name: seaking
119.description: It is the male’s job to make a nest by carving out boulders in a stream using the horn on its head.

120.name: staryu
120.description: As long as the center section is unharmed, this Pokémon can grow back fully even if it is chopped to bits.

121.name: starmie
121.description: The center section is named the core. People think it is communicating when it glows in seven colors.

122.name: mr-mime
122.description: Always practicing its pantomime act. It makes enemies believe something exists that really doesn’t.

123.name: scyther
123.description: Leaps out of tall grass and slices prey with its scythes. The movement looks like that of a ninja.

124.name: jynx
124.description: Appears to move to a rhythm of its own, as if it were dancing. It wiggles its hips as it walks.

125.name: electabuzz
125.description: If a major power outage occurs, it is certain that this Pokémon has eaten electricity at a power plant.

126.name: magmar
126.description: Born in an active volcano. Its body is always cloaked in flames, so it looks like a big ball of fire.

127.name: pinsir
127.description: Grips its prey in its pincers and squeezes hard! It can’t move if it’s cold out, so it lives in warm places.

128.name: tauros
128.description: A rowdy Pokémon with a lot of stamina. Once running, it won’t stop until it hits something.

129.name: magikarp
129.description: Famous for being very unreliable. It can be found swimming in seas, lakes, rivers, and shallow puddles.

130.name: gyarados
130.description: Brutally vicious and enormously destructive. Known for totally destroying cities in ancient times.

131.name: lapras
131.description: A gentle soul that can understand human speech. It can ferry people across the sea on its back.

132.name: ditto
132.description: When it spots an enemy, its body transfigures into an almost-perfect copy of its opponent.

133.name: eevee
133.description: It can evolve into a variety of forms. Eevee’s genes are the key to solving the mysteries of Pokémon evolution.

134.name: vaporeon
134.description: Its cell structure is similar to water molecules. It melts into the water and becomes invisible.

135.name: jolteon
135.description: A sensitive Pokémon that easily becomes sad or angry. Every time its mood changes, it charges power.

136.name: flareon
136.description: It has a flame chamber inside its body. It inhales, then breathes out fire that is over 3,000 degrees Fahrenheit.

137.name: porygon
137.description: The only Pokémon that people anticipate can fly into space. None has managed the feat yet, however.

138.name: omanyte
138.description: An ancient Pokémon that was recovered from a fossil. It swam by cleverly twisting its 10 tentacles about.

139.name: omastar
139.description: Its sharp beak rings its mouth. Its shell was too big for it to move freely, so it became extinct.

140.name: kabuto
140.description: A Pokémon that was recovered from a fossil. It used the eyes on its back while hiding on the seafloor.

141.name: kabutops
141.description: A slim and fast swimmer. It sliced its prey with its sharp sickles and drank the body fluids.

142.name: aerodactyl
142.description: A savage Pokémon that died out in ancient times. It was resurrected using DNA taken from amber.

143.name: snorlax
143.description: Will eat anything, even if the food happens to be a little moldy. It never gets an upset stomach.

144.name: articuno
144.description: A legendary bird Pokémon. It freezes water that is contained in winter air and makes it snow.

145.name: zapdos
145.description: This legendary bird Pokémon is said to appear when the sky turns dark and lightning showers down.

146.name: moltres
146.description: A legendary bird Pokémon. As it flaps its flaming wings, even the night sky will turn red.

147.name: dratini
147.description: Long thought to be a myth, this Pokémon’s existence was only recently confirmed by a fisherman who caught one.

148.name: dragonair
148.description: According to a witness, its body was surrounded by a strange aura that gave it a mystical look.

149.name: dragonite
149.description: It is said that this Pokémon lives somewhere in the sea and that it flies. However, these are only rumors.

150.name: mewtwo
150.description: Its DNA is almost the same as Mew’s. However, its size and disposition are vastly different.

151.name: mew
151.description: When viewed through a microscope, this Pokémon’s short, fine, delicate hair can be seen.
